metadata.name: FxPlanet #469
metadata.description:
üü¢„Ä∞Storyline„Ä∞üü¢

Once upon a time, a God had a little daughter. The daughter liked to explore the planets on his father's cosmos. Suddenly the daughter got sick and died like a collapsing star. God gets alone, angry, depressed and finally mad. He turned all the universe to ash and mixed the ash of her daughter's soul with it to make her alive, But he failed. In the end, he decided to destroy himself to make a New cosmos of all generative planets from ash of himself and his daughter's soul to one more time in the eternity they can be with each other in a heart of a planet. If you listen carefully to the planets, you may hear them calling each other.

‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ‚¨õ

üî¥„Ä∞Rarity„Ä∞üî¥

This collection is a 3D generative interactive artwork (Made with Unity Game Engine) that contains of 9999+1 planets (1 shared source of light and 9999 pieces of souls) from billions of variation. You can see more random variations from fxhash page.
‚óº The beauty and complexity of the Planet's surface is important, But what is going on inside?
Each planet has three grades of volume (High, Medium, Low) that show you what resources exist on the planets (Common, Rare, Legendary).
Some resources are so valuable and infrequent.
‚óº For Example: It's possible to get Oxygen (Legendary Resource) on Low volume slot, but it's infrequent if you get it on High volume slot.
‚óº Checkout Material rarity list on webpage.

metadata.name: Uninhabitable #302
metadata.description:
Uninhabitable is a generative system built only from ellipses. The process of playing with different geometric and trigonometric disruptions gives rise to four different compositions which seek to evoque living constructions and environments. Besides the shape itself and its related distortion, the stroke weight of the lines plays a meaningful role in the piece. Following a discrete range [0.01,0.1,1] the weight reveals the process allowing the viewer to realize the trace of the huge amount of lines in each piece. This back and forth between scales and context is, while kind of stripping the code, part of my continuing interest on understanding the -usually- crazy paths of machines' way of thinking.

Press "h" to see it and high resolution and refresh to get back to the initial state. Press "h" to save it.

Uninhabitable is an original work by Iskra Velitchkova. 2021.

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #716
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 1 #424
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ 0.1, ____ 0.2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: Grid Return #1
metadata.description:
With "Grid Return" (Sept. 2022), I revisit the conceptual territory of my genesis work, "Grid Meditations" (Jan. 2022).

The four tenets of the Grid that I proclaimed eight months ago still ring true for me today:

1. The grid is the ultimate tool of abstraction.

2. The grid rejects any imitation of depth.

3. The grid exposes the true nature of the canvas as a two-dimensional surface.

4. The grid both imposes order and allows for the legibility of disorder.

metadata.name: Gradilines #12
metadata.description:
Each line has a different gradient. The lines line up in a square or a parallelogram. Then squares and parallelograms are lined up in a certain pattern.
Either it's an intertwining of stripes, or the squares are randomly rotated 90 degrees, or ...
Please see the variations.

______
by neigal 18.04.22

metadata.description:
There is a mystery in the lifeline, where we walk and discover all alone. Some landscapes make we breath this solitude.

- 17 palettes available.
- 2 Styles of landscapes (Desert and Sea).
- 2 Colors of Sea (Red and Blue).
- The Desert may contain cactus.

Press the [S] key in live view to save a "Lines of solitude".jpg file.

This artwork was created with p5.js
